.TH "dma_sb_map_area_linear" 9 "dma_sb_map_area_linear" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dma_sb_map_area_linear \- Map an area of memory into a device dma region.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dma_sb_map_area_linear
.BI "(struct ps3_dma_region *r "  ","
.BI "unsigned long virt_addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long len "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *bus_addr "  ","
.BI "u64 iopte_flag "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "r" 12
Pointer to a struct ps3_dma_region.
.IP "virt_addr" 12
Starting virtual address of the area to map.
.IP "len" 12
Length in bytes of the area to map.
.IP "bus_addr" 12
A pointer to return the starting ioc bus address of the area to
map.
.IP "iopte_flag" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine just returns the corresponding bus address.  Actual mapping
occurs in \fBdma_region_create_linear\fP.
